This has the same error message as https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/10176, I have no idea if it's related.

A similar error was hit in http://buildbot.rust-lang.org/builders/auto-win-32-opt/builds/1002/steps/compile/logs/stdio

I also got the error while trying to `make check-fast` https://github.com/retep998/rust/tree/c619884972a91caa3536e62d2f4198a349ea0828
Unfortunately I'm on win64 where unwind info broke again _sigh_, so RUST_BACKTRACE doesn't work and gdb just gives me garbage.

```

make: *** [x86_64-w64-mingw32/stage2/test/nativetest-x86_64-w64-mingw32.exe] Error 101
```

So far I have this, probably: A [match in callee.rs](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/15765/files#diff-2567497dc7ace5d97add7371c5b720e3R143) is recognizing some extern fns defined in other crates as named tuple constructors. #15765 has been merged 5 days before this issue was opened.

cc @luqmana
A [small patch by @pczarn](https://github.com/pczarn/rust/commit/c96c52fdca4249ecbf93f0ea3741908391153f94) has fixed the ICE I was getting.
